</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,258,1441]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,330,1308,1333]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285">Taxonomy.</emphasis>
The taxon shares the following characters with taxa of nominative subgenus: antennal pits broadly separated, eyes covered with dense hairs, not very dense hairs on body and all habitus is similar with other members of 
<emphasis box="[292,466,1380,1404]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="285">
<taxonomicName box="[292,399,1380,1404]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="285" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" sensu="stricto">Cheilosia</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[406,466,1381,1404]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285" sensu="stricto">s. str.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
In the key to Chinese 
<taxonomicName authority="Barkalov &amp; Cheng 2004" authorityName="Barkalov &amp; Cheng" authorityYear="2004" box="[720,1130,1380,1405]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="285" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[720,828,1380,1404]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="285">Cheilosia</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Barkalov" box="[842,1122,1380,1405]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285" refString="Barkalov, A. V. &amp; Cheng, X. - Y. (2004) Revision of the genus Cheilosia Meigen, 1822 (Diptera: Syrphidae) of China. Contributions on Entomology, International, 5 (3 / 4), 266 - 421." type="journal article" year="2004">
Barkalov &amp; Cheng 
<number box="[1064,1122,1381,1405]" pageId="5" pageNumber="285" value="2004.0">2004</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
